            "content": "<p><small>Tebtebba is an indigenous peoples` organization and a research, education, policy advocacy and resource center working with indigenous peoples at all levels and areas. They seek the recognition, promotion and protection of indigenous peoples` rights and aspirations while building unions to uphold social and environmental justice and sustainability.</small><p><strong>POTENTIAL CONTRIBUTION TO THE NETWORK:</strong></p><ul>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Provide resource speakers and subject matter experts for Indigenous peoples issues and relevant information:</p>\r\n\r\n\t<ul>\r\n\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t<p>IPs Rights</p>\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t<p>IPs and Climate Change</p>\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t<p>IPs and Gender</p>\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t<p>IPs and Sustainable Development</p>\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t<p>IPs and Biodiversity and others</p>\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul><p><strong>INSTITUTIONAL DEVELOPMENT AND CAPACITY BUILDING SERVICES:</strong></p><ul>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<ul>\r\n\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t<p>Training and Workshops for Indigenous People`s issues and concerns.</p>\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul><p><strong>AVAILABLE RESOURCES (that can be shared to the network)</strong></p><ul>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Learning Resource Materials for researches and information.</p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Expertise to issues and concerns about Indigenous Peoples</p>\r\n\r\n\t<ul>\r\n\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t<p>can be a resource person / subject matter expert in seminars, forums, conventions and trainings.</p>\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul></p>\n",
