            "content": "<p><small>NMS-Cares is a nonprofit organization registered and incorporated with the Philippine Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) August of 2014 with registration number CN201427490. It started as a corporate social responsibility initiative to help Deaf children&rsquo;s education in 2012 by Martin Eyking and his family, founder and CEO of New Media Services Pty. Ltd., an Australian-based IT company with operations in the Philippines.</small><p><strong>POTENTIAL CONTRIBUTION TO THE NETWORK:</strong></p><ul>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Organization of Training for:</p>\r\n\r\n\t<ul>\r\n\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t<ul>\r\n\t\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t\t<p>Sign Language Seminars and Forums</p>\r\n\t\t\t</li>\r\n\t\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t\t<p>Deaf Awareness</p>\r\n\t\t\t</li>\r\n\t\t</ul>\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Provide a Subject Matter Experts on Seminars, Forums, Training and Workshops concerning matters critical to the deaf community.</p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul><p><strong>INSTITUTIONAL DEVELOPMENT AND CAPACITY BUILDING SERVICES:</strong></p><ul>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Conduct of Sign Language Skills Training</p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Conduct of Deaf Awareness and Sensitivity Training, Seminars and Forums</p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Conduct of Deaf Sports Development</p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul><p><strong>AVAILABLE RESOURCES (that can be shared to the network)</strong></p><ul>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<ul>\r\n\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t<p>Human resource &ndash; we can share our expertise in line with Deaf Awareness, Sensitivity Training and Seminars, Sign Language Skills Development and Disability Advocacies.</p>\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul></p>\n",
